            3. I deserve the talent scout to give me a chance as I performed my standup routine in front of the audience. (Reasonable)<br/>
            4. I deserve the talent scout to give me a contract as I performed my standup routine in front of the audience. (Unreasonable)<br/><br/>

            1. I’m entitled to see a take a photograph of a lion because I bought tickets to the huge state zoo. (Reasonable)<br/>
            2. I’m entitled to feed a lion because I bought tickets to the huge state zoo. (Unreasonable)<br/>
            3. I’m entitled to see a lion because I bought tickets to the huge state zoo. (Reasonable)<br/>
            4. I’m entitled to see a lion give birth because I bought tickets to the huge state zoo. (Uneasonable)<br/><br/>

            1. I merit a nice cold beer reward from my fridge because I had a hard day’s work at the factory. (Reasonable)<br/>
            2. I merit a nice cold beer reward from my fridge because I had a hard day’s work attending my junior high classes. (Unreasonable)<br/>
            3. I merit a nice cold beer reward from my neighbor because it's his turn to buy beer when we hang out tonight. (Reasonable)<br/>
            4. I merit a nice cold beer reward from my neighbor because I had a hard day’s work at the factory. (Unreasonable)<br/><br/>

            1. I am justified in expecting my wife not to quickly gain 200 pounds now that we just married. (Reasonable)<br/>
            2. I am justified in expecting my wife to quickly gain 200 pounds now that we just married. (Unreasonable)<br/>
            3. I am justified in expecting my wife to remember to brush her teeth. (Reasonable)<br/>
            4. I am justified in expecting my wife to remember to brush my teeth. (Unreasonable)<br/><br/>
